metrics.name: PRICE
metrics.formula: Current closing price of the stock
metrics.usage_notes: Primary reference point for all other indicators

metrics.name: SMA_20
metrics.formula: Simple Moving Average over 20 periods
metrics.bullish_signal: Price above SMA_20 with positive slope
metrics.bearish_signal: Price below SMA_20 with negative slope
metrics.usage_notes: Short-term trend indicator; acts as dynamic support/resistance

metrics.name: SMA_50
metrics.formula: Simple Moving Average over 50 periods
metrics.bullish_signal: Price above SMA_50; SMA_20 > SMA_50 (golden cross)
metrics.bearish_signal: Price below SMA_50; SMA_20 < SMA_50 (death cross)
metrics.usage_notes: Intermediate-term trend; strong signal when crossed

metrics.name: SMA_200
metrics.formula: Simple Moving Average over 200 periods
metrics.usage_notes: Long-term trend; primary bull/bear market indicator

metrics.name: EMA_20
metrics.formula: Exponential Moving Average over 20 periods (more weight on recent prices)
metrics.bullish_signal: Price above EMA_20 with upward slope
metrics.bearish_signal: Price below EMA_20 with downward slope
metrics.usage_notes: More responsive than SMA_20 to recent price changes

metrics.name: EMA_50
metrics.formula: Exponential Moving Average over 50 periods
metrics.usage_notes: Intermediate trend with faster reaction than SMA_50

metrics.name: SMA_20_SLOPE
metrics.formula: Rate of change of SMA_20 over 5 periods: (SMA_20[t] - SMA_20[t-5]) / SMA_20[t-5]
metrics.usage_notes: Indicates trend momentum; positive = strengthening uptrend

metrics.name: SMA_50_SLOPE
metrics.formula: Rate of change of SMA_50 over 5 periods: (SMA_50[t] - SMA_50[t-5]) / SMA_50[t-5]
metrics.usage_notes: Longer-term trend momentum; more reliable than SMA_20_SLOPE

metrics.name: RSI
metrics.formula: Relative Strength Index: 100 - (100 / (1 + RS)) where RS = Avg Gain / Avg Loss over 14 periods
metrics.usage_notes: Classic overbought/oversold indicator; divergence with price is powerful

metrics.name: RSI_DIVERGENCE
metrics.formula: RSI minus 5-period moving average of RSI
metrics.bullish_signal: Positive divergence (price makes lower low but RSI doesn't)
metrics.bearish_signal: Negative divergence (price makes higher high but RSI doesn't)
metrics.usage_notes: Indicates weakening momentum; precedes reversals

metrics.name: STOCHASTIC_K
metrics.formula: 100 * (Close - Low14) / (High14 - Low14) where High14/Low14 are 14-period highs/lows
metrics.usage_notes: Shows position within recent range; fast-moving oscillator

metrics.name: STOCHASTIC_D
metrics.formula: 3-period SMA of STOCHASTIC_K (signal line)
metrics.usage_notes: Slower signal line; crossovers indicate momentum shifts

metrics.name: WILLIAMS_R
metrics.formula: -100 * (High14 - Close) / (High14 - Low14)
metrics.usage_notes: Inverse of Stochastic; measures overbought/oversold conditions

metrics.name: MACD
metrics.formula: 12-period EMA minus 26-period EMA
metrics.usage_notes: Trend-following momentum indicator; crossovers are key signals

metrics.name: MACD_SIGNAL
metrics.formula: 9-period EMA of MACD
metrics.usage_notes: Signal line for MACD; crossovers generate buy/sell signals

metrics.name: MACD_HISTOGRAM
metrics.formula: MACD minus MACD_SIGNAL
metrics.usage_notes: Shows strength of MACD signal; divergence indicates weakening trend

metrics.name: RETURN_24H
metrics.formula: Percentage price change over last 24 hours: (Price[t] / Price[t-24]) - 1
metrics.usage_notes: Recent price momentum; useful for identifying short-term trends

metrics.name: RETURN_48H
metrics.formula: Percentage price change over last 48 hours: (Price[t] / Price[t-48]) - 1
metrics.usage_notes: 2-day momentum; stronger signal than RETURN_24H

metrics.name: RETURN_168H
metrics.formula: Percentage price change over last 168 hours (1 week): (Price[t] / Price[t-168]) - 1
metrics.usage_notes: Weekly momentum; critical for weekly predictions; shows established trends

metrics.name: VOLATILITY_20
metrics.formula: Annualized standard deviation of log returns over 20 periods * sqrt(252*24)
metrics.usage_notes: Recent volatility; higher values = more risk and opportunity

metrics.name: VOLATILITY_60
metrics.formula: Annualized standard deviation of log returns over 60 periods * sqrt(252*24)
metrics.usage_notes: Longer-term volatility baseline; compare with VOLATILITY_20 for regime changes

metrics.name: ATR
metrics.formula: Average True Range: 14-period average of max(High-Low; High-Close[t-1]; Close[t-1]-Low)
metrics.bullish_signal: Low ATR with price consolidation before breakout
metrics.usage_notes: Absolute volatility measure; useful for stop-loss placement

metrics.name: ATR_RATIO
metrics.formula: ATR divided by current price: ATR / Close
metrics.bearish_signal: Very high ATR_RATIO (> 0.03) suggesting unstable conditions
metrics.usage_notes: Normalized volatility; easier to compare across stocks

metrics.name: BB_POSITION
metrics.formula: Position within Bollinger Bands: (Close - BB_Lower) / (BB_Upper - BB_Lower)
metrics.usage_notes: Shows position in volatility envelope; < 0.2 = oversold, > 0.8 = overbought

metrics.name: BB_WIDTH
metrics.formula: Width of Bollinger Bands: BB_Upper - BB_Lower
metrics.bearish_signal: Widening width (high volatility) after large move
metrics.usage_notes: Band compression indicates low volatility; precedes significant moves (Bollinger Squeeze)

metrics.name: VOLUME_RATIO
metrics.formula: Current volume divided by 20-period average volume
metrics.usage_notes: Confirms price moves; volume should support direction for validity

metrics.name: OBV
metrics.formula: Cumulative volume: Add volume on up days; subtract on down days
metrics.bullish_signal: OBV trending up while price consolidates
metrics.bearish_signal: OBV trending down while price consolidates
metrics.usage_notes: Tracks money flow; divergence from price indicates smart money accumulation/distribution

metrics.name: OBV_DIVERGENCE
metrics.formula: OBV minus 20-period moving average of OBV
metrics.bullish_signal: Positive divergence (rising OBV with falling/flat price)
metrics.bearish_signal: Negative divergence (falling OBV with rising/flat price)
metrics.usage_notes: Shows whether volume confirms price action; divergence precedes reversals

metrics.name: VWAP_DEVIATION
metrics.formula: Percentage deviation from VWAP: (Close - VWAP) / VWAP
metrics.usage_notes: Institutional traders reference; price above VWAP = buyers in control

metrics.name: PRICE_POSITION_168H
metrics.formula: Position within 168-hour (1 week) range: (Close - Low168) / (High168 - Low168)
metrics.usage_notes: Shows position in weekly range; < 0.3 = support zone, > 0.7 = resistance zone

metrics.name: DIST_FROM_RESISTANCE
metrics.formula: Distance from 50-period resistance: (Resistance - Close) / Close
metrics.usage_notes: Shows room to move up; smaller values = near resistance (potential reversal)

metrics.name: DIST_FROM_SUPPORT
metrics.formula: Distance from 50-period support: (Close - Support) / Close
metrics.usage_notes: Shows downside risk; smaller values = near support (potential bounce)

metrics.name: PRICE_TO_SMA20
metrics.formula: Price divided by SMA_20
metrics.usage_notes: Shows short-term trend strength; > 1.02 = strong uptrend

metrics.name: PRICE_TO_SMA50
metrics.formula: Price divided by SMA_50
metrics.usage_notes: Shows intermediate trend strength; > 1.05 = solid uptrend

metrics.name: SMA20_TO_SMA50
metrics.formula: SMA_20 divided by SMA_50
metrics.usage_notes: Moving average alignment; > 1.02 = strong bullish alignment
